On the $MU Conference Call.
$MU Conference Call: We can see why the stock has been hammered, looks like Bit Growth DRAM sales down 12%, Bit GrowthNAND Sales down 7%.
$MU Conference Call: Although, all together, DRAM only down 2% for the combined entity & NAND down 3%.
$MU Conference Call: Notebook, desktop commodity DRAM business was soft heading into Q4.
$MU Conference Call: $MU to recieve $275 Million from Samsung in a 10 year Cross-Licensing deal announced today.
$MU Conference Call: $40 Million in idle facility charged on the quarter; compared to $18 Million in Q3.
$MU Conference Call: On the quarter R&D $197 M, SG&A $141M, OpEx, $338 Million; $1.1 Billion in cash flow from operations.
$MU Conference Call: Free cash flow is $2.15 Billion, over $3Billion in cash & reduced debt by over $600 Million.
$MU Conference Call: Numonyx integration next year/quarter means that we will not be able to see breakdown of two companies.
$MU Conference Call: Diluted EPS $0.32 as reported and $0.37 as adjusted with Numonyx.
$MU Conference Call: Speaking of people who have both an iPhone and an iPad, people would rather use the iPad for a number of reasons.
$MU Conference Call: If people are going to continue to move towards the tablets, then wireless infrastructure will need to be increased.
$MU Conference Call: Our NAND segment plays into the growing tablet & we think NAND upside is very strong.
$MU Conference Call: We also think servers, blades, & other infrastructure will be good for both DRAM and NAND going forward.
$MU Conference Call: Earlier in the year we weren't seeing any weakness in consumer electronics, it was really supply driven.
$MU Conference Call: We are certainly expecting weakness for this holiday season in consumer electronics.
$MU Conference Call: Looking around the world though, Europe is improving, Asia is still pretty strong.
$MU Conference Call: Something has to happen on the demand side in order for us to see stronger pricing in Feburary of 2011.
$MU Conference Call: We had wafers up a couple percent from August and expect the same in the next month.
$MU Conference Call: Channel inventory on DRAM is up to the 4 or 5 weeks in the supply channel; NAND is about 3 to 4 weeks.
$MU Conference Call: Back to school just happened late, and it wasn't all that bad...general retail OK, & about what we saw in the channel.
$MU Conference Call: We are more bullish on the retail space than someone looking at the raw desktop or notebook.
$MU Conference Call: We've targeted OpEx for 15% and we are doing much better than that.
$MU Conference Call: Less and less of our product is in the commodity ASP arena & we continue to improve this mix.
$MU Conference Call: We are the only company in DRAM that continued to have a positive operating cash flow through the entire cycle.
$MU Conference Call: Back to school did happen for us later, so August did look weak on paper since there was a shift in consumber purchases
